[normal]Written evidence submitted by the Royal Meteorological Society (IPC0029)[bold]Description of submission[bold]1. This submission is made on behalf of the Royal Meteorological Society (RMetS). 
[normal]The Royal Meteorological Society is the Learned and Professional Society for weather and climate. The Society is a registered charity. Its affairs are run by a Council of Trustees. Council comprises a total of nineteen Officers and Ordinary Members of Council elected at the Annual General Meeting.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2. The submission was drafted by the Chair of the 
[normal]RMetS’s
[normal] Climate Science Communications Group (CSCG), incorporating comments from the CSCG members and members of Council. It has been approved by RMetS Council.
[normal] A list of members of the CSCG and of Council are provided in
[normal] Note 1 
[normal]below. 
[normal]3. The inquiry invites comments with regard to the IPCC’s fifth assessment report (AR5). Our responses refer specifically to the report of Working Group 1 (WG1).
